"Abstract The last two years has seen a number of high profile disposals of licences for spectrum for 3G mobile services and Wireless Local Loop (WLL) (including Broadband Fixed Wireless (BFW)). Disposals such as the German and UK 3G licence auctions attracted front-page news because of the astronomical figures involved. Others (Italy, for example) attracted attention because of their collapse. Regulators are claiming collusion in auctions, the industry is claiming that beauty parades are preferable, that auctions are placing too great a financial strain on their business and financial markets are reflecting the industry view. This article provides a guide to countries disposing of spectrum and focuses on the disposal of licences for 3G mobile services and BFW services."
